# Line-ending policy: the repo is LF in the index (every tracked text file — 2279/2279
# — is stored LF; there are zero CRLF blobs). Force LF on CHECKOUT everywhere so a
# Windows machine with core.autocrlf=true does not materialize CRLF working-tree files.
#
# WHY THIS EXISTS: CI (.github/workflows/verify.yml) runs `runs-on: windows-latest`, and
# GitHub's Windows runner images set core.autocrlf=true by default. Without this file,
# `actions/checkout` rewrote LF blobs to CRLF on disk, which broke byte-exact tests
# (tests/gemini_api_build_determinism.test.js compares the module file to a hard-coded
# '\n'-wrapped string) and could perturb render-digest goldens. The blobs are unchanged;
# this only normalizes how they land on disk. Matches what dev machines already produce
# (build scripts write LF).
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binaries: never apply text/EOL conversion (explicit, in addition to git's auto-detect).
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.webp binary
*.ico  binary
*.bmp  binary
*.pdf  binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf  binary
*.otf  binary
*.eot  binary
*.mp3  binary
*.mp4  binary
*.wav  binary
*.m4a  binary
*.zip  binary
*.gz   binary
*.wasm binary
